    <note>Chen(1) Shengzhi [77] His original mingzi, Xu, was changed to avoid Shenzong's mingzi. For much of family history, see Jingkou qi jiu zhuan, 1.6b-7a and Zhishun Zhenjiang zhi, 19.5b-6a. Shengzhi brought his second cousin, Jian(6) [21307], second nephews, Yu(2) [14328] and Zhen(4) [14333], with him when he moved to Zhenjiang. Shengzhi's only grandson, Jing(6) [14332], died without male progeny and Shengzhi ordered that Xi(3)'s [14329] younger brother (&amp; his 2nd nephew) act as Shengzhi's heir or descendant. Zhen(4)'s only son Qi (not in dataset) apparently also died without male offspring and Xi(3)'s great great grandson became Shengzhi's heir or descendant. See also documentation for collateral descendant, Jiayan [21309]. Jia Zhenjiang, 18.12b; XCB, 173.1a-1b, 175.17a, 191.14b, 245.1a; XCBSB, 4.4b, 6.1a,; SHY:ZG, 5.1a, 23.7b; SS, 12.16b. CBD, 3, 2553-4.</note>
